pullRequest.body:
Defines universal and existential formulas
Proves preservation results for universal and existential formulas
As an application, shows that substructures of models of the theory of linear orders are also models of the theory of linear orders.

<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
```

Right now, it seems that showing that a specific formula has a specific complexity level requires manually recreating the definition of the formula.
I'd like that to be more automated, perhaps with instance resolution, and I'd happily take suggestions on that.
I've realized that the preservation results here should probably be proven at the level of, say, `StrongHomClass` - see #16107 and #16108.
